race.comment: Time for the Cup now and OPPORTUNISTIC (1) is easy to put on top. He hasn't shown the zip we saw in his 3YO campaign, with the rise to 1920m now looking suitable for him. He's obviously a classy galloper however, starting favourite in a strong race last time out. Likely to get back from the draw, but can stay over the top of them late. GINGER GREEN (3) hasn't been far away recently, finishing 1.3L off the winner over 1800m at Ascot most recently. Faithfull replaces the apprentice hoop in a good push for his chances. Rates highly off that latest effort and he looks the main danger. ROCKING SOCIETY (2) was just 1L off the winner 22 days ago at Ascot when racing over the mile. The step right up to 1920m looks good however with his racing style and Fiore sticks with him. Can sit handy and land the knockout blow. CANDLELIGHT SUPPER (7) has to be included off a strong performance last time out. AUTUMN REBEL (5) looks suited by the rise in trip today and is not to be discounted.
